<isis lang="en">
    <stitle>DT/DTA-466 Diesel Engine Service (1990) - CYLINDER HEAD AND VALVES - CYLINDER HEAD REMOVAL - CLEANING
    </stitle>
    <svcman/>
    <svcproc svcproctype="clean" graphiccount="2">
        <title>CLEANING</title>
        <step1>
            <para count="1">With the valves installed to protect the seats, remove deposits and gasket material from the
                gasket surface of the cylinder head using a rotary wire brush or sanding block with mineral spirits.
                <emph type="bold">BE SURE INJECTION NOZZLES ARE REMOVED BEFORE WIRE BRUSHING, TO PREVENT INJECTION
                    NOZZLE DAMAGE.
                </emph>
            </para>
        </step1>
        <step1>
            <para count="1">Clean all bolt holes with a tap. Clear debris from bolt holes, oil return and water
                passages, using filtered compressed air.
            </para>
        </step1>
        <step1>
            <para count="1">Clean the cylinder head bolt threads with a bristle brush.</para>
        </step1>
        <step1>
            <para count="1">Wash all bolts and washers with a suitable solvent and dry thoroughly.</para>
            <specpara>
                <note>
                    <para>Dirt in threads or damaged threads may cause binding and result in a false torque reading.
                    </para>
                </note>
            </specpara>
            <figure id="ef4150414" figsize="col-wide">
                <graphic id="cg11542" filename="../figcg1/cg11542.webp" type="webp"/>
                <caption>Figure 4.14. Break Cylinder Head Gasket Seal.</caption>
            </figure>
            <figure id="ef4150415" figsize="col-wide">
                <graphic id="cg11706" filename="../figcg1/cg11706.webp" type="webp"/>
                <caption>Figure 4.15. Remove Cylinder Head.</caption>
            </figure>
        </step1>
    </svcproc>
